  "response": "Yes, 20 years old is generally considered young. It is often seen as a transitional age, where individuals are moving from adolescence into adulthood. At this age, many people are still exploring their identities, pursuing education or early career opportunities, and developing their relationships and life skills. Different cultures and contexts may perceive age differently, but in many societies, 20 is still seen as part of youth.",
